			A member's score in each event is their rank in that event multiplied by the following points: 
			<ul>
				<li>5 mile run = 1 point</li>
				<li>12 mile ruck = 2 points</li>
				<li>100 meter dash = 3 points</li>
				<li>Pull-ups (total in 2 min) = 4 points</li>
				<li>Push-ups (total in 2 min) = 4 points</li>
				<li>Dips (# in 2 min) = 4 points</li>
				<li>Squat (% of bodyweight) = 5 points</li>
				<li>Bench (% of bodyweight) = points</li>
				<li>Deadlift (% of bodyweight) = points</li>
				<li>Overhead Press (% of bodyweight) = 5 points</li>
			</ul>
			A member's total score is the sum of the scores in each event. A lower total score yields a better overall rank.
		</div>

		


